.TH "pm_clk_notify" 9 "pm_clk_notify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_clk_notify \- Notify routine for device addition and removal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pm_clk_notify
.BI "(struct notifier_block *nb "  ","
.BI "unsigned long action "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nb" 12
Notifier block object this function is a member of.
.IP "action" 12
Operation being carried out by the caller.
.IP "data" 12
Device the routine is being run for.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For this function to work, \fInb\fP must be a member of an object of type
struct pm_clk_notifier_block containing all of the requisite data.
Specifically, the con_ids member of that object is used to enable or disable
the device's clocks, depending on \fIaction\fP.
